LoanData by Prosper¶

by Temitope Balogun¶

Introduction¶

Prosper is a US based lending marketplace, with over $21 billion in funded loans. Prosper generates revenue by collecting a one-time fee on funded loans from borrowers and assessing an annual loan servicing fee to investors. Borrowers can apply online which makes the process seamless. This dataset consists of 113,937 loans.

Borrower Rate¶

  • Similar of BorrowerAPR, BorrowerRate is also multimodal with the highest interest rate at 34%. #### Prosper Score
  • Prosper Score is unimodal with highest points at 4, 6 and 8.
  • According to Data Dictionary, Prosper Score is a custom risk score. The score ranges from 1-10, with 10 being the best, or lowest risk score. Surprisingly, there are scores for 11

  • The Higher the loan, the lower the charges paid by the Borrower

Conclusions¶

After investigating Proper loan, Below observations were deduced

  • High prosper score Borrowers are likely to get low interest rates.
  • High number of Borrowers use loan collected to service other Debts(Debt Consolidation).
  • Top Borrowers are from California, New York and Texas.
  • Borrowers who have high Prosper score tend to be granted high sum of loan.
  • Borrowers who are employed have high chances of getting loan.
